TI  - Handbook of Cross-Cultural Management
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 310
EP  - 311
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
AB  - The scholarly research of international business is going through continuous transformation as multinational firms and comparative management evolve in a changing global economy, with theoretical frameworks re-evaluated. Recently, several teams of editors have sought to record the progress, to define the field of international business, and to outline future direction of inquiry by publishing handbooks with contributions by the who-is-who in the field. The latest additions to this bookshelf are the Oxford Handbook of International Business (OHIB), the Blackwell Handbook of Cross-Cultural Management, and a symposium based volume Emerging Issues in International Business Research, edited by Mike Kotabe with similar objectives.
